/KASHIR HAKAVOD / SONG OF GLORY/PR
/ITThe ark is opened./PR
/PR
These melodies I sing, now weaving lines of song,/PR
for only for your presence does my spirit sorely long./PR
My soul desires nothing but your handÚs protective shield,/PR
to know all secret paths within the mystery that is sealed./PR
/PR
Each time I speak of glory, in this world or above,/PR
my heart is full of longing for your friendship and your love./PR
Therefore I only speak of you with glory-singerÚs tongue,/PR
I glorify your name with songs that those in love have sung./PR
/PR
And so I tell your glory, yet never have seen you;/PR
imagine you, find names for you, yet never have known/PR
you./PR
By hand of those who prophesied and throngs who/PR
worshipped you,/PR
you gave imagination to the glory beyond view./PR
/PR
GodÚs greatness now unfolding, your might beyond all/PR
needs,/PR
they found the names for telling of the power of your/PR
deeds./PR
Denoting you with likenesses, though less than you by far,/PR
they simply have equated what youÚve done with who you/PR
are./PR
/PR
HereÚs parable and proverb and endless visions sung,/PR
and yet, beyond all imagery, behold, you are one./PR
With age you now appear to some, to some a youngster/PR
fair,/PR
each person tells the whiteness or the blackness of your/PR
hair./PI/PR
