/PG462/XX/PR
In Israel none arose/PR
as prophet like Moshe,/PR
a prophet who would come to see/PR
the "image" in the /ITsneh/XX./PR
Torah of truth God gave/PR
the people IsraÚel,/PR
by truest prophetÚs hand/PR
that in GodÚs house would dwell./PR
/PR
And God will never let/PR
the Torah pass away,/PR
its doctrine will not change,/PR
but through all change will stay./PR
God sees and knows all things,/PR
and even what we hide,/PR
can look upon how things begin/PR
the end of things to find,/PR
/PR
Rewarding acts of love,/PR
when love for love weÚll find,/PR
and paying to all wickedness/PR
a recompense in kind,/PR
God shall deliver all,/PR
upon the end of time,/PR
redeeming all who wait for God,/PR
who for salvation pine./PR
/PR
God wakes all beings to life,/PR
abundant love shall reign,/PR
blessed evermore,/PR
the glory of GodÚs Name!/PR
