/PG464/XX/PR
/KAKIDDUSH RABAH LESHABBAT ULYOM TOV //PR
/XXKIDDUSH FOR SHABBAT AND FESTIVAL/PR
MORNINGS/PR
/ITThis version of Kiddush is recited between the end of the morning service and the beginning
of lunch./PR
/PR
On every Shabbat begin here:/PR
/PR
Let IsraelÚs descendants keep Shabbat, making Shabbat
throughout all their generations, as an eternal bond. Between
me and IsraelÚs descendants shall it be a sign eternally. For in six
days /SCT/XXHE /XXV/XXOICE/XX made skies and earth, and on the seventh day
God ceased and drew a breath of rest./PR
And so /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXMINENCE/XX blessed the day of Shabbat and made it
holy./PR
/ITOn Pesah/±, Shavuot, and Sukkot say:/PR
/PR
Moses proclaimed the Festivals of /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXNDURING /XXO/XXNE/XX to the
children of Israel./PR
/ITWhen Shabbat coincides with a festival, recite the sections for both. Morning Kiddush always
concludes with the following blessing:/PR
/PR
With the permission of this company:/PR
/PR
Blessed are you, /SCT/XXHE /XXB/XXOUNDLESS /XXO/XXNE/XX, our God, the sovereign
of all worlds, who creates the fruit of the vine./PR
